one kafka consumer is overloaded while others are idle

what's happening
you run a kafka consumer group with multiple instances
kafka should split work evenly, but in reality one consumer is overloaded while other stay idle

even after scaling consumers the system remains slow

why this happens(real causes)
this is partition skew, not a kafka bug

Uneven key distrubution (most common)
messages with the same key always go to the same partition.
if most traffic goes to one key or partition. the consumer it becomes overloaded.

common reasons
	one hevy coustumer/device
	null or constant keys
	poor key choice(eg. timestamp)
	very few unique keys

too few partations
if partations < consumers some consumers stay idel
kafka cannot split one partation across multiple consumers

sticky partation assigment
kafka tries to keep partations on the same consumer after rebalances
heavy partations may stick to one consumer, cuasing long-term imbalance

host key inside a partation
even with balanced partations one dominant key can overloaded a consumer

no parallelsim per partation
kafka allows one thread per partation
cpu-heavy or db-heavy processing slow the consumer

what skew looks like

one partation recieves most of the traffic
consumer owing it is overloaded
other cosumers stay mostly idle

dubbign steps

check consumer group assigment
use kafka-consumer-groups --describe to see partation and lag distribution

check partation traffic
identity partations with high message volume or large-payloads

review messges keys
ensure keys re evenly distributed and high-cardinaliyt

inspect consumer processing
look for slow db calls or heavy cpu work

compare partations vs consumers
partitions should be greater than or equal to consumers

how to fix it (archtect solutions)

inrease partition count(most effective)
imporve key design (avoid null, constant, timestamp key)
tune partition assignor(range or cooperativsticky)
add internal parallelsim(worker threads, async processing)
force rebalance(restart or redeploy consumers)
use kafka strams repartiton when applicable

takeaway
kafka scales by partitons not consumers
balanced keys and enough partitons are the key to even load distribution


